Thailand Stocks: Bangkok Chain, Land & Houses, Siam Industrial

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-03-21T05:47:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/bumrungrad-bangkok-chain-bangchak-ptt-thai-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 12:30 p.m. lunch break in
Bangkok.  The SET Index rose 9.01, or 0.9 percent, to 1,012.30.  Land & Houses Pcl (LH TB), Thailand’s biggest home builder
by market value, climbed 3.7 percent to 5.55 baht, set for the
largest increase since Feb. 17. Land & Houses sold its 24.99
percent stake in  Bangkok Chain Hospital Pcl (KH)   for 3.53
billion baht ($116.6 million), the company said in a regulatory
filing on March 18.  Bumrungrad Hospital Pcl (BH)  bought Bangkok
Chain’s shares at 8.50 baht each.  Bumrungrad (BH TB), the nation’s second-largest listed
hospital operator, gained 0.7 percent to 35.75 baht. Bangkok
Chain rose 2.1 percent to 7.30 baht, on course for the highest
close since it listed in 2004.    Siam Industrial Credit Pcl (SICCO)  , a financial company,
increased 3.8 percent to 4.36 baht, on course for the steepest
advance since March 3.  Siam Commercial Bank Pcl (SCB) , Siam
Industrial’s biggest shareholder, plans to hold a public auction
for its stake in the financial company, it said in a regulatory
filing today. Siam Commercial (SCB TB), Thailand’s fourth-
biggest lender by assets, rose 0.5 percent to 102 baht.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
